examples.en: She swung the door open.
The heavy door swung shut.

Politicians have already swung into action.
His emotions swung between fear and curiosity.
The batter swung and missed.
The sheets swung on the clothesline.
She swung her legs from side to side.
She swung her bag at him.
A gold chain swung free around his neck.
Guido swung the steering-wheel round to negotiate a corner.
He heaved on the steering wheel and swung the car into a side street.
She swung her purse at me.
The gates swung silently open.

He swung at the ball, but didn't connect.
